title: Emma Jenkins
text:
Emma Victoria Jenkins (born 1993 in <a href="Llanelli">Llanelli</a>, <a href="Wales">Wales</a>) is a <a href="Welsh%20people">Welsh</a> television presenter and beauty pageant titleholder who was crowned <a href="Miss%20Universe%20Great%20Britain%202019">Miss Universe Great Britain 2019</a>. She represented Great Britain at <a href="Miss%20Universe%202019">Miss Universe 2019</a>.
Pageantry.
Emma Jenkins went to compete in <a href="Miss%20Wales">Miss Wales 2015</a> and placed first. As <a href="Miss%20Wales">Miss Wales</a>, she represented <a href="Wales">Wales</a> at <a href="Miss%20World%202015">Miss World 2015</a> where she finished unplaced.
Jenkins was a finalist at <a href="Miss%20Universe%20Great%20Britain">Miss Universe Great Britain 2017</a> but decided to withdraw from the competition. On 13 July 2019 she won the <a href="Miss%20Universe%20Great%20Britain%202019">Miss Universe Great Britain 2019</a> competition at the Mercure Holland House in <a href="Cardiff">Cardiff</a>, <a href="Wales">Wales</a> and was crowned by outgoing titleholder <a href="Dee-Ann%20Kentish-Rogers">Dee-Ann Kentish-Rogers</a>.
She represented Great Britain in the <a href="Miss%20Universe%202019">Miss Universe 2019</a> competition and finished unplaced.
